<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-07T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-07T14:00:00-05:00" n="1295" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1295">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/324</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-07T12:00:00-07:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 7, 1917, noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Repayment promised July 15, but promise is not believed. Merchants there
                            greatly depressed by increasing excessive business tax in addition to
                            general loan.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>